cs.HC, cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CC

This paper belongs to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category as it focuses on the usability and security of graphical pattern lock schemes on smartphone devices. It also falls under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it discusses the guessing resistance of different pattern lock schemes. Additionally, it could be categorized under Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it deals with securing user authentication on mobile devices. The paper also involves Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) as it analyzes the stroke length and memorability of different pattern lock schemes. Lastly, it could be classified under Computation and Language (cs.CC) as it involves the study of user behavior and decision-making in the context of graphical pattern lock schemes.
